ACTION SA leader Herman Mashaba will lead a picket outside the Department of Mineral Resources and Energy
Minister Gwede Mantashe’s Head Quarters in Sunnyside, Tshwane on Tuesday. On 19
May 2022, the Lily Mine Families
as well as former miners and workers marched to the offices of the Premier of
Mpumalanga, Refilwe Mtshweni-Tsipane and delivered a memorandum requesting her
Office’s intervention to have a meeting with the Mine’s Business Rescue
Practitioners who have to date not delivered on their mandate as ordered by the
Mbombela High Court. It
was requested that the Premier’s Office respond within 10 days of receipt of
the memorandum which it failed to do. READ: LILY MINE SORROW CONTINUES! Lerato Ngobeni
said in a statement, “ActionSA, as supporters of the Lily
Mine Families since Mashaba was approached during the People’s Dialogue, soon
after his resignation as the Mayor of Joburg December 2019, will, together with
a 100 member-strong team accompany the families to Minister Mantashe’s Offices
to escalate and lay their issues at his doorstep as the chief accounting officer
of the State in this regard.” Mashaba
will accompanied by John Moodey,
ActionSA National Director of Operations; Bongani Baloyi, ActionSA Gauteng Provincial Chairperson; Lerato Ngobeni, ActionSA National
Spokesperson as well as ActionSA Caucus Leaders in Gauteng Metros: Funzi Ngobeni; Derrick Kissonduth; and Tlhogi
Moseki. Most importantly, families and representatives of the Lily Mine
Families led by Official Family Spokesperson, Harry Mazibuko.